 So each y_i comes from a normal distribution independent and identically distributed with the normal distribution. With mean \mu and variance \sigma^2. This specifies a probability distribution and a model for the data.y_i \stackrel{iid}\sim N(\mu,\sigma^2) \ i \in 1 \dots N






